Vestel Beyaz Buys Brands From Italy’s Merloni, Hurriyet Reports

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-09-05T06:26:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/vestel-beyaz-buys-brands-from-italy-s-merloni-hurriyet-reports.html
Vestel Beyaz Esya Sanayi & Ticaret
AS, a Turkish household appliances maker owned by Zorlu Holding
AS, acquired four brands from  Italy ’s Antonio Merloni SpA,
 Hurriyet  reported, citing Vestel Deputy Chief Executive Turan Erdogan.  The company, which bought the Servis, Electra, Atlantic and
New Pool home appliance brands, plans to raise annual exports to
$1 billion a year in three years from a forecast $750 million
this year, the Istanbul-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 